Package org.jboss.windup.config

Interface RuleLifecycleListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRuleLifecycleListener, ArchiveIdentificationLifecycleListener, ArchivePackageNameIdentificationLifecycleListener, FileMappingLifecycleListener, ProjectTraversalCache, RuleExecutionResultsListener, TypeInterestFactoryLifecycleListener
    public interface RuleLifecycleListener
    Receives events from RuleSubset during execution.

    Lincoln Baxter, III, Ondrej Zizka

      • shouldWindupStop

        default boolean shouldWindupStop()
        Returns directly the information whether Windup execution should stop. Not all listeners need to return true - just one returning true is a reason to stop execution. Queried by various rule implementations so we can stop as soon as possible.
